## Commit

```bash
git add -A
git commit -m "feat(admin): v2.38.0 Analysis view — templated SQL diagnostics

New sith_lord-only view under ADMIN that lets operators run registered
SQL queries for deep-diving operations/sessions/entities and download
the results as JSON, CSV, or Markdown.

BACKEND: new api/analysis_templates.py registers 7 parameterized SQL
templates (operation_full_context, session_all_operations,
recent_failures, tool_error_frequency, escalations_detail,
entity_recent_attempts, fact_history). New api/routers/analysis.py
mounts /api/admin/analysis/{templates,run,dump} behind the
require_sith_lord dependency (reuses existing role_meets()). Queries
run via psycopg with SET LOCAL statement_timeout=30_000ms plus a
template-declared row_cap enforced as LIMIT (max 10,000). Param
validation coerces types (uuid / int / text) and enforces
required/min/max from the template schema; unknown keys in the request
body are silently dropped. Named %(name)s placeholders only — a
structural test fails CI if bare %s appears in any template SQL.

FRONTEND: new gui/src/components/AnalysisView.jsx renders the catalog
as a dropdown, builds a param form from each template's schema, shows
results as a collapsible JSON tree, and downloads via
Content-Disposition. 403 handled gracefully with a role-required
notice. New sidebar entry under ADMIN; AnalysisView wired into the
App.jsx view dispatcher.

SAFETY: templates-only — no freeform SQL in v1. All queries are
parameterized (psycopg %(name)s placeholders), so SQL injection is not
possible through this path. list_templates() never returns raw SQL to
the client — only {id, title, description, params, row_cap}.
statement_timeout + row_cap + sith_lord gate are belt-and-braces.

TESTS: 9 pure unit tests in tests/test_analysis_templates_catalog.py
cover template schema validity, positional-placeholder prohibition,
param validation (required, uuid, int bounds, default fill,
row_cap clamping, unknown-key dropping). Auth shape tests in
tests/test_analysis_router_auth.py confirm 401 on unauthenticated
requests to every endpoint; role-gap tests skip gracefully if
auth fixtures aren't available.

No schema changes. No new Settings keys. No external dependencies
(psycopg, FastAPI, already present).

Post-ship followup queued: v2.38.1 can add a freeform SQL mode behind
'analysisFreeformEnabled' Settings flag (default False) using a
dedicated read-only DB role — or more templates as operators discover
needs. Also: wire a 'Copy operation_id to Analysis' button from Trace
viewer for one-click deep-dive. Neither blocks v2.38.0."
git push origin main
